Based on the exploratory analysis and model training, the features that influenced house prices the most were **area**, **number of bathrooms**, **air conditioning**, and **preferred area**, as they showed a stronger relationship with the target variable. The Linear Regression model was able to predict prices reasonably well and captured the overall trend of the data, although some individual predictions had noticeable errors. One surprising observation was that amenities such as air conditioning and location preference could significantly increase the predicted house price, even when other features were similar. The analysis also showed that larger houses with more facilities generally commanded higher prices. Based on these findings, a real estate business should focus on properties in preferred locations with modern amenities and emphasize these features in marketing to attract buyers and maximize value.
